Introduction to the Point-of-Use Water Treatment Systems Market
Point-of-use (POU) water treatment systems are designed to purify drinking water at the point of consumption. These systems are used in households, commercial establishments, and industries to provide safe and clean drinking water by eliminating contaminants such as bacteria, viruses, heavy metals, and chemicals. The increasing concerns regarding water contamination, rising health awareness, and the demand for convenient and affordable water purification solutions are driving the growth of the POU water treatment systems market globally.
