Market Segmentation
The POU water treatment systems market is segmented based on technology, product type, application, and region.
By Technology
1.	Reverse Osmosis (RO) – Removes dissolved solids, heavy metals, and contaminants.
2.	Ultrafiltration (UF) – Effective against bacteria and viruses but retains essential minerals.
3.	Ultraviolet (UV) Purification – Kills microorganisms using UV radiation.
4.	Activated Carbon Filters – Removes chlorine, organic compounds, and odors.
5.	Ion Exchange Technology – Reduces water hardness and heavy metals.
6.	Distillation – Boils water and condenses pure steam, eliminating impurities.
By Product Type
1.	Countertop Filters – Portable and easy-to-install filtration units.
2.	Under-Sink Filters – Installed under kitchen sinks for continuous purification.
3.	Faucet-Mounted Filters – Compact and affordable water filters attached to faucets.
4.	Pitcher Filters – Simple and portable water purification solutions.
5.	Tabletop and Wall-Mounted Purifiers – Ideal for households and commercial use.
6.	Portable Water Filters – Designed for outdoor, travel, and emergency use.
By Application
1.	Residential – Households seeking clean and safe drinking water.
2.	Commercial – Offices, restaurants, and hotels requiring high-quality water.
3.	Industrial – Factories and manufacturing units using purified water in processes.
By Region
1.	North America (U.S., Canada)
2.	Europe (Germany, UK, France, Italy, Spain)
3.	Asia-Pacific (China, Japan, India, South Korea)
4.	Rest of the World (RoW)
